3-112:In the following section, we reduce this cost by relaxing the expensive requirements of SVMs. .
4 RELAXED ONLINE SVMS (ROSVM) :
4-1:One of the main benefits of SVMs is that they find a decision hyperplane that maximizes the margin between classes in the data space .
4-2:Maximizing the margin is expensive, typically requiring quadratic training time in the number of training examples .
4-3:However, as we saw in the previous section, the task of content based spam detection is best achieved by SVMs with a high value of C .
4-4:Setting C to a high value for this domain implies that minimizing training loss is more important than maximizing the margin (see Figure 3) .
4-5:Thus, while SVMs do create high performance spam filters, applying them in practice is overkill .
4-6:The full margin maximization feature that they provide is unnecessary, and relaxing this requirement can reduce computational cost .
4-7:We propose three ways to relax Online SVMs: • Reduce the size of the optimization problem by only optimizing over the last p examples .
4-8:• Reduce the number of training updates by only training on actual errors .
