5-67:4.3 Discussion The comparison results shown in Tables 5, 6, and 7 are striking in two ways .
5-68:First, they show that the performance of Online SVMs can be matched and even exceeded by relaxed margin methods .
5-69:Second, they show a dramatic disparity in computational cost .
5-70:ROSVM is an order of magnitude more efficient than the normal Online SVM, and gives comparable results .
5-71:Furthermore, the fixed lookback buffer ensures that the cost of each update does not depend on the size of the data set already seen, unlike Online SVMs .
5-72:Note the blog and splog data sets are relatively small, and results on these data sets must be considered preliminary .
5-73:Overall, these results show that there is no need to pay the high cost of SVMs to achieve this level of performance on contentbased detection of spam .
5-74:ROSVMs offer a far cheaper alternative with little or no performance loss. .
